# AdventureScenario Card Usage

## Summary
The `AdventureScenario` card represents a scenario or episode within an adventure narrative. It contains information about the scenario, including a title, description, tags, and visual styling hints.

## Import
```javascript
import { AdventureScenario } from 'http://localhost:4201/richardtan/richy-workspace/adventure-00dd63cf-3bdf-431c-910d-1a99d423fd5c/adventure/adventure-scenario';
```

## Usage as a Field
To use the `AdventureScenario` card as a field within a consuming card or field, you can define it as follows:

```javascript
import { CardDef, field, linksTo } from 'https://cardstack.com/base/card-api';
import { AdventureScenario } from 'http://localhost:4201/richardtan/richy-workspace/adventure-00dd63cf-3bdf-431c-910d-1a99d423fd5c/adventure/adventure-scenario';

export class MyCard extends CardDef {
  @field adventure = linksTo(AdventureScenario);
}
```

## Template Usage
To display an `AdventureScenario` card within a consuming template, you can use the following:

```handlebars
{{#if @model.adventure}}
  <@fields.adventure @format="embedded" />
{{else}}
  <div class="empty-state">No adventure scenario selected</div>
{{/if}}
```

This will render the `AdventureScenario` card in its embedded format, or display a placeholder if no scenario is available.
